Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getObjFPlanPolygon(25.10)                            getObjFPlanPolygon(25.10)

Name
       getObjFPlanPolygon  -  Retrieves  polygon  coordinates of the specified
       rectilinear object that was created earlier with the setObjFPlanPolygon
       command

Syntax
        getObjFPlanPolygon

       [-help]

       type

       name

       Retrieves polygon coordinates of the specified rectilinear object  that
       was  created  earlier  with the setObjFPlanPolygon command. You can use
       this command after setting the polygon  coordinates  of  a  rectilinear
       block with the setObjFPlanPolygoncommand.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each getObjFPlanPolygon  parameter.  For  a  de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man getObjFPlanPolygon

       <name> Specifies the name of the object for type.

              Data_type: string, required

       <type> Specifies the type of object for objectName. This can be:

              * Cell

              * Group

              * Instance

              * Layer shape

              * Module

              Data_type: string, required

Example
       The following command retrieves the polygon coordinates of module xyz.

       getObjFPlanPolygon module xyz

Related Information
              * setObjFPlanPolygon

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

